  <section>
    <h2 class="heading-l">Font families</h2>
    <p>Three font family tokens covering body, heading, and monospace uses. All default to system font stacks — replace them in your application <code>:root</code> to load a custom typeface.</p>

    
    <div class="padding-m margin-y-m background-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200">
<div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem; padding-block: 0.5rem;">
  <div>
    <p style="font-family: var(--font-family); font-size: var(--font-size-m);">The quick brown fox — <code>--font-family</code></p>
    <p style="color: var(--color-neutral-500, #6d6d6d); font-size: var(--font-size-xs);">-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, "Fira Sans", "Droid Sans", "Helvetica Neue", sans-serif</p>
  </div>
  <div>
    <p style="font-family: var(--font-family-heading); font-size: var(--font-size-m); font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.02em;">The quick brown fox — <code>--font-family-heading</code></p>
    <p style="color: var(--color-neutral-500, #6d6d6d); font-size: var(--font-size-xs);">Inherits <code>--font-family</code> by default — override to use a display typeface</p>
  </div>
  <div>
    <p style="font-family: var(--font-family-mono); font-size: var(--font-size-s);">const greeting = "Hello, world"; — <code>--font-family-mono</code></p>
    <p style="color: var(--color-neutral-500, #6d6d6d); font-size: var(--font-size-xs);">SFMono-Regular, Consolas, "Liberation Mono", Menlo, Courier, monospace</p>
  </div>
</div>
    </div>

    <details class="margin-y-s">
      <summary class="padding-s">Show code</summary>
      <pre class="padding-m background-neutral-900" style="overflow-x: auto;"><code>&lt;div style=&quot;display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem; padding-block: 0.5rem;&quot;&gt;
  &lt;div&gt;
    &lt;p style=&quot;font-family: var(--font-family); font-size: var(--font-size-m);&quot;&gt;The quick brown fox — &lt;code&gt;--font-family&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;p style=&quot;color: var(--color-neutral-500, #6d6d6d); font-size: var(--font-size-xs);&quot;&gt;-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Fira Sans&quot;, &quot;Droid Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div&gt;
    &lt;p style=&quot;font-family: var(--font-family-heading); font-size: var(--font-size-m); font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.02em;&quot;&gt;The quick brown fox — &lt;code&gt;--font-family-heading&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;p style=&quot;color: var(--color-neutral-500, #6d6d6d); font-size: var(--font-size-xs);&quot;&gt;Inherits &lt;code&gt;--font-family&lt;/code&gt; by default — override to use a display typeface&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div&gt;
    &lt;p style=&quot;font-family: var(--font-family-mono); font-size: var(--font-size-s);&quot;&gt;const greeting = &quot;Hello, world&quot;; — &lt;code&gt;--font-family-mono&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;p style=&quot;color: var(--color-neutral-500, #6d6d6d); font-size: var(--font-size-xs);&quot;&gt;SFMono-Regular, Consolas, &quot;Liberation Mono&quot;, Menlo, Courier, monospace&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
    </details>

    <p>To use a custom typeface, define the token in your application after importing the library:</p>
    <pre><code>@import url("https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;700&display=swap");

:root {
  --font-family:         "Inter", sans-serif;
  --font-family-heading: "Inter", sans-serif;
}</code></pre>
  </section>

