  <section>
    <h2 class="heading-l">Measure (line length)</h2>
    <p>Measure tokens control the maximum line length of text containers. Optimal reading measure for body text is 45–75 characters, which is the intent of <code>--width-l</code>.</p>

    
    <div class="padding-m margin-y-m background-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200">
<div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem; padding-block: 0.5rem;">
  <div>
    <p style="font-size: var(--font-size-xs); color: var(--color-neutral-500, #6d6d6d); margin-block-end: 0.25rem;">--width-s: 35ch — labels, narrow columns</p>
    <p style="max-width: var(--width-s); background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-status-ok, #1a4) 10%, transparent); padding: 0.5rem; border-radius: 0.25rem;">Account holder full name as it appears on the payment card.</p>
  </div>
  <div>
    <p style="font-size: var(--font-size-xs); color: var(--color-neutral-500, #6d6d6d); margin-block-end: 0.25rem;">--width-l: 65ch — optimal body text measure</p>
    <p style="max-width: var(--width-l); background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-status-ok, #1a4) 10%, transparent); padding: 0.5rem; border-radius: 0.25rem;">Fluid typography eliminates the need for discrete breakpoints. Instead of jumping between fixed font sizes at specific viewport widths, each token interpolates smoothly across the defined range using the CSS <code>clamp()</code> function.</p>
  </div>
  <div>
    <p style="font-size: var(--font-size-xs); color: var(--color-neutral-500, #6d6d6d); margin-block-end: 0.25rem;">--width-wide: 100% — full container width</p>
    <p style="max-width: var(--width-wide); background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-status-ok, #1a4) 10%, transparent); padding: 0.5rem; border-radius: 0.25rem;">This paragraph spans the full width of its container, suitable for data tables, banners, or any content that benefits from maximum horizontal space.</p>
  </div>
</div>
    </div>

